# Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your values.

## Discord (Required)

```bash
# Discord Bot Token
# Get from: https://discord.com/developers/applications > Bot > Token
DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=

# Discord Application ID (Client ID)
# Get from: https://discord.com/developers/applications > General Information
DISCORD_CLIENT_ID=

# Discord OAuth2 Client Secret
# Get from: https://discord.com/developers/applications > OAuth2
DISCORD_CLIENT_SECRET=
```

## Database (Required)

```bash
# PostgreSQL connection string
# Format: postgresql://user:password@host:port/database
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://fattips_user:your_password@localhost:5432/fattips

# For Docker setup:
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://fattips_user:your_password@postgres:5432/fattips
```

## Solana (Required)

```bash
# Solana RPC URL
# Mainnet: https://mainnet.helius-rpc.com/?api-key=YOUR_API_KEY
SOLANA_RPC_URL=https://mainnet.helius-rpc.com/?api-key=

# Master Encryption Key (32 bytes, base64 encoded)
# Generate with: openssl rand -base64 32
MASTER_ENCRYPTION_KEY=
```

## Jupiter (Required)

```bash
# Jupiter Price API URL
# Get API key from: https://portal.jup.ag
JUPITER_API_URL=https://api.jup.ag/price/v3

# Optional: Jupiter API Key (for higher rate limits)
# Leave blank for free tier (may have limited functionality)
JUPITER_API_KEY=
```

## Smart Contract (Required for Phase 2+)

```bash
# Airdrop program ID (after deployment)
# Devnet: 
# Mainnet: 
AIRDROP_PROGRAM_ID=
```

## Web Dashboard (Required for Phase 8)

```bash
# NextAuth Secret (random string)
# Generate with: openssl rand -base64 32
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=

# NextAuth URL
# Development: http://localhost:3000
# Production: https://codestats.gg
NEXTAUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000
```

## Optional

```bash
# Log Level (debug, info, warn, error)
# Default: info
LOG_LEVEL=info

# API Port
# Default: 3001
PORT=3001

# Web Port
# Default: 3000
WEB_PORT=3000

# Bot Prefix (for legacy commands if any)
# Default: !
BOT_PREFIX=!

# Admin API Key (for admin endpoints)
ADMIN_API_KEY=
```

## Getting Helius API Key

1. Go to https://www.helius.xyz/
2. Sign up for free account
3. Create new endpoint
4. Copy the RPC URL (includes your API key)

## Security Notes

- NEVER commit `.env` file
- NEVER share your DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN
- NEVER share your MASTER_ENCRYPTION_KEY
- Keep backups of encryption keys in secure location
- Rotate API keys periodically
